    <h3>NSW Government colour palette</h3>
    <p>The NSW Government colour palette contains 10 colours sets (each with four different tones), plus black and white. The palette is made up of:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Colour sets</strong> - each column, or set of four colours within the same family.</li>
      <li><strong>Tonal sets</strong> - each row, 01 being the darkest tonal set and 04 being the lightest tonal set.</li>
      <li><strong>Dark colours</strong> - colours that meet 4.5:1 contrast ratio with Text Light #FFFFFF.</li>
      <li><strong>Light colours</strong> - colours that meet 4.5:1 contrast ratio with Text Dark #22272B.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Colour Usage Levels</h3>
    <p>There are three colour theming levels in NSW Government:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Level 01 (Masterbrand Level 1 and 2)</li>
      <li>Level 02 (Materbrand Level 3 and Co-Brand)</li>
      <li>Level 03 (Independent)</li>
    </ul>
