    <h3>Changing Brand colours for Level 01</h3>
    <p>The only defined colour for Level 01 is Blue 01, and others can be adopted following the colour usage rules below:</p>
    <p>If you wish to change a variable colour, it must be selected from the Blue, Red or Grey colour sets and:</p>
    <p><strong>Brand Light</strong> must be a Light colour (accessible with Text Dark).</p>
    <p><strong> Brand Supplementary</strong> must be a Dark colour (accessible with Text Light).</p>
    <p><strong> Brand Accent</strong> can be selected from any row in wider colour palette (Row 02 and 03 recommended).</p>
    <p>Guidance on applying these in Figma can be found on the Colours page of the <a href="">Figma UI Kit</a>.</p>

    <h3>Changing Brand colours Level 02 and 03</h3>
    <p>Level 02 and 03 colour usage have access to the full colour palette for all Brand colours. This includes Masterbrand Level 3, Co-brand and Independent. Once you have chosen your new brand colours, use the steps below to apply them to a digital palette. </p>
    <p><strong>Brand Dark</strong> must be selected from Row 01.</p>
    <p><strong>Brand Light</strong> must be a Light colour (accessible with Text Dark).</p>
    <p><strong> Brand Supplementary</strong> must be a Dark colour (accessible with Text Light). This is an additional colour option only available if your Brand Light is not from Row 02.</p>
    <p><strong> Brand Accent</strong> can be selected from any row from your chosen colour sets (Row 02 and 03 recommended).</p>
   
   <h3>Apply new colours to Brand palette</h3>
   <p>Guidance on applying your new Brand colours in Figma can be found on the Colours page of the <a href="">Figma UI Kit</a>.</p> 
   <p>As foundations and components inherit colours from the base colour theme, changing a Brand colour will automatically filter down to all instances where that colour is used. Alternatively, colour instances can be updated on an individual basis as required. Where this possible, it is indicated in the guidance on the Components page.</p>




